I have updated the firmware for my ESP32-S3 UHF RFID Handheld. Please update the existing Web Bluetooth JavaScript code (API handling) to match the new protocol specifications below.

1. BLE Service & Characteristics:

Service UUID: 0x00FF

Command/Control Characteristic (Read/Write/Notify): 0xFF01

Role: Used for sending commands (Start/Stop) and receiving Live Stream Data (EPC + RSSI).

File Data Characteristic: 0xFF03 (Not used for Live mode, ignore for now).

2. Sending Commands (App -> Device via 0xFF01): Please update the control buttons to send these exact JSON strings (UTF-8 encoded):

Start Live Scan: {"cmd":"S"}

Stop Live Scan: {"cmd":"X"}

Start Batch Scan (Offline): {"cmd":"SB"}

Stop Batch Scan: {"cmd":"XB"}

Set Power (e.g., 30dBm): {"cmd":"SP","val":30}

Get Power: {"cmd":"GP"}

3. Receiving Data (Device -> App via Notify on 0xFF01): The device now sends data in batches of 3 tags to optimize MTU. The format has changed from a simple array of strings to an array of objects containing both EPC and RSSI.

New JSON Format:

JSON
{
  "cmd": "live_tags",
  "tags": [
    { "e": "E280116060000213966A4875", "r": -65 },
    { "e": "E280116060000213966A4876", "r": -70 },
    { "e": "E280116060000213966A4877", "r": -62 }
  ]
}
Key e: EPC Hex String.

Key r: RSSI (Integer, usually negative, e.g., -60 dBm).

4. UI Requirements:

Parse the incoming JSON from 0xFF01.

If cmd is live_tags, loop through the tags array.

Update the UI to display the EPC and its corresponding RSSI.

(Optional) If a tag already exists in the list, update its RSSI value; otherwise, add it to the list.

(Optional) Show a visual indicator (like a progress bar or color) based on the RSSI value (Signal strength).

Please rewrite the handleNotifications function and the command sending functions to adapt to this new V7.0 JSON protocol.

